COMMONLY USED COMMAND EXAMPLES

1)  Creating a New Branch
cvs checkout -r kuntz_dock dock  #download the code from Master Branch
cvs tag -b kuntz_dock_solvation  #create new branch
cvs update -r kuntz_dock_solvation  #move onto new branch
cp ~/solvation/salt.cpp src/  #copy over modified files (if necessary)
cvs add salt.cpp -r kuntz_dock_solvation  #add new files (if necessary)
cvs commit -r kuntz_dock_solvation  #commit new changes to branch
cvs update -A -d  #get back to an up to date trunk

2)  Adding New Code
cvs -nq update -r kuntz_dock  #note out of date files/possible conflicts
cvs update -d  #update the code
cvs diff -c #prints out contextual differences between new and old code
vi  ...  #edit files with unresolved conflicts 
cvs commit -r kuntz_dock  #commit new code

3)  Merging from Trunk to Branch
cvs co -r shoichet_dock dock  #pull down files from branch
cvs -nq update -r HEAD        #dryrun of pull down files from tip of trunk
cd dock/src                   #enter directory where files you want to merge
                              #  are located
cvs update -j HEAD score.cpp  #pull down only the source code file you
                              #  want to merge
cvs diff -c  #write out difference between merged file and file version 
             #  on branch (output can be used to generate files for use 
             #  with the "patch" command)
vi score.cpp #make changes to file if necessary
cvs commit -r shoichet_dock   #if happy with merge, save to branch

4)  Other Frequently Used Commands
cvs diff -c              #indicates differences between versions
cvs log                  #print the log file
cvs status -v            #prints the status and tags of file
cvs tag -r post_bugfix1  #adds tag to all files


